Stoke City assistant manager Mark Bowen has revealed that Bayern Munich attacker Xherdan Shaqiri is a surprise transfer target for the club.

Inter Milan are the firm favourites for the 23-year-old who is due to hold discussions with Bayern officials on Wednesday morning. 

'To get a good player like him on board would be fantastic,' Bowen told Radio Stoke on Tuesday.

