The Reds, however, are reluctant to spend now and would prefer to look at a deal in the summer instead.

Inter have offered £2million for a loan deal, similar to the one proposed to Arsenal for Lukas Podolski, but Bayern want to sell outright and would like Liverpool to come to the table. 

Erdin, Xherdan's agent, wants to see if Bayern will accept a loan deal to Inter now with the prospect of joining Liverpool in the summer.

Bayern are still on their winter break but the player's immediate future should come to a conclusion after Wednesday's meeting. 

 

